b"      Dear all  Warm wishes from NSS family!  NSS IITM joins hands with Ability Foundation, Chennaito bring to you the first skill development workshop of the semester: Sign Language Workshop . Sign language is a language which chiefly uses manual communication to convey meaning. This involves hand shapes, orientation and movement of hands, arms or body and facial expressions to express a speaker's thoughts .   Ability Foundation is involved in pioneering activities, ranging from publishing and media, counselling and referral services, advocacy, and training and employment. Over the years, the Foundation has organized several events all of which aim at dispelling stereotypes and changing public attitudes/perceptions towards disabled persons. Find more about Ability Foundation at    Event Details   Date       :   October 2016, Saturday  Time      :  : 00 am to 1:00 pm  Venue      :  Central Lecture Theatre (CLT)  For any queries feel free to contact Deva Nandan 9940127112                      ;    Sourav Rames 944467371    To all volunteers, it's always a 'credit' to know a language. Sodo turn up for theevent with your id cards.  Thanks and Regards, Managerial team, NSS IIT Madras  Website:  www.nss.iitm.ac.in Facebook:  www.facebook.com/nss.iitm     "

